font.docstring:
Font specification as a CSS-like string.
Format: "[bold] [italic] <size>pt <family>"
- Size must be in points (pt), NOT pixels (px). Use 10-12pt for readable text.
- Common sizes: 10pt (small), 11pt (default), 12pt (standard), 14pt (headers)
@example "12pt Arial" - Standard readable font
@example "bold italic 14pt Arial" - Bold italic header

copyRangeFromWorkbook.docstring:
Copies a range of cells from one workbook to another, including values, formulas, and formatting.
This function preserves all cell properties including styles, number formats, and formulas.
Range addresses MUST include sheet names.
@param fromWorkbook - Source workbook object (use "workbook" for main, "attachedWorkbook" for attached)
@param fromRange - Source range address with sheet name. Must have sheet name (e.g., "Sheet1!A1:D10")
@param toWorkbook - Target workbook object (use "workbook" for main, "attachedWorkbook" for attached)
@param toRange - Target range address with sheet name. Must have sheet name (e.g., "Sheet2!B2") - only the top-left cell is needed

copyRangeFromWorkbook.signature:
copyRangeFromWorkbook(
    fromWorkbook: any,
    fromRange: string,
    toWorkbook: any,
    toRange: string
  ): void;

calculate.docstring:
Recalculate values in the entire workbook.
IMPORTANT: Writing operations do not trigger recalculation until after code execution completes. If you want to read values immediately after writing values, you MUST call this function.
@example
worksheet.setCell("A1", 100);
worksheet.calculate();
console.log(worksheet.getCell("A1")); // 100

addNamedRange.docstring:
Add a named range to the workbook (always workbook-scoped).
@param name - The name for the range
@param reference - The Excel reference (e.g., "$A$1" or "Sheet1!$A$1:$B$10")
@param comment - Optional comment describing the named range
@example workbook.addNamedRange("TotalRevenue", "Sheet1!$D$10", "Sum of all revenue");

removeNamedRange.docstring:
Remove a named range from the workbook or sheet.
@param name - The name of the range to remove
@param scope - Optional scope: "workbook" (default) or specific sheet name
@example workbook.removeNamedRange("TotalRevenue");

addChart.docstring:
Add a chart to the sheet with sensible defaults
@param name - Unique name for the chart
@param chartType - Type of chart (Column, Line, Pie, etc.)
@param dataRange - Excel range containing the data (e.g., "A1:B10"). Also supports multi-select ranges (e.g., "A1:B10,D1:E10"). Note: sheet names containing commas are not supported.
@param options - Optional configuration
  - dataOrientation: Whether data series are in rows or columns (default: "columns")
  - categoryIndex: 0-based index of the column/row to use as category labels (e.g., 0 for first column)

addChart.signature:
addChart(
    name: string,
    chartType: ChartType,
    dataRange: string,
    options?: { dataOrientation?: 'rows' | 'columns'; categoryIndex?: number }
  ): void;

addTable.docstring:
Convert a range to a table.
@param range - The Excel range to convert to a table (e.g., "A1:D10").
@param tableName - The name to assign to the new table.
@param hasHeaders - Whether the range includes header rows.
@param style - Optional table style (e.g., "TableStyleLight1", "TableStyleMedium1", "TableStyleDark1")

autoFill.docstring:
Autofill function equivalent to Excel's drag-fill. Adjusts formula references, detects patterns (1,2,3→4,5,6), works in all directions.
Applies source formatting to target range. Use 'constant' mode to copy without incrementing.
@param sourceRange - Cell/range containing the pattern
@param targetRange - Range to fill
@param fillMode - 'auto' (default) detects patterns, 'constant' copies without incrementing
@example sheet.autoFill("B1", "B2:B10"); // Formula =A1*2 becomes =A2*2, =A3*2, etc.
@example sheet.autoFill("A1:C1", "A2:C10"); // Autofill multiple columns at once
@example sheet.autoFill("D1", "D2:D10", "constant"); // Copies value as-is

goalSeek.docstring:
Performs Goal Seek analysis to find the input value that produces a desired output.
Goal Seek adjusts a variable cell value until a formula cell reaches the specified goal value.

@param variableAddress - Excel address of the cell to adjust (e.g., "B3")
@param formulaAddress - Excel address of the cell containing the formula (e.g., "B4")
@param goalValue - The target value for the formula cell
@returns True if Goal Seek found a solution, false otherwise

@example
// Find interest rate that results in $600 monthly payment
sheet.setCell("B1", 10000);  // Loan Amount
sheet.setCell("B2", 18);     // Term in Months
sheet.setCell("B4", "PMT(B3/12,B2,B1)"); // Payment formula
sheet.goalSeek("B3", "B4", -600); // Adjust B3 until B4 equals -600

addPicture.docstring:
Add a picture/image to the sheet from a base64-encoded string.
@param name - Unique name for the picture
@param base64Data - Base64-encoded image data (PNG or JPEG). Do NOT include the "data:image/png;base64," prefix.
@param anchorCell - The cell where the top-left corner of the image will be anchored (e.g., "A1")

@example
await sheet.addPicture("revenue_chart", store.chart_base64, "F2");

regexSearch.signature:
regexSearch(
    patterns: string[],
    options?: { matchCase?: boolean }
  ): { address: string; value: any }[];

addPivotTable.docstring:
Add a pivot table to the sheet.
IMPORTANT: Do not add any additional fields to the pivot table that are not specified by the user.
IMPORTANT: Row fields and column fields must be ordered hierarchically from broadest to most specific.

@param config - Pivot table configuration
@returns Object containing the pivot table name, content area range, and filter area range

addPivotTable.signature:
addPivotTable(config: PivotTableConfig): {
    name: string;
    contentArea: string;
    filterArea: string;
  };

freezeFirstRows.docstring:
Freezes the first rows from the top of the sheet.
@param count - The number of rows to freeze from the top
@example sheet.freezeFirstRows(1); // Freeze the first row (header row)

setIBTextColors.docstring:
Apply Investment Banking (IB) model text color conventions to a range of cells. Only applies to cells containing numeric values or formulas that produce numbers.
- Blue (default: #0000FF): hard-coded numeric values
- Black (default: #000000): formulas
- Green (default: #008000): referencing other sheets within the workbook
To prevent the colors from being applied to certain cells, especially thoes containing header numbers, such as years, quarters, etc., use the ignoredConstants parameter.
@param range - The range to apply colors to (e.g., "A1:D10")
@param ignoredConstants - Array of numeric constants to skip when applying colors (e.g., [0, 1, 2, 100]). These values will retain their existing formatting.
@param colors - Optional custom colors object for input, formula, and cross-sheet references

setIBTextColors.signature:
setIBTextColors(
    range: string,
    ignoredConstants?: number[],
    colors?: {
      inputColor?: string;
      formulaColor?: string;
      crossSheetColor?: string;
    }
  ): void;

setRowVisibleAt.docstring:
Set visibility of the row specified by rowAddress.
WARNING: Do NOT hide rows that contain data used by charts unless explicitly requested by the user. Hiding chart source data causes charts to render blank/white.
@example setRowVisibleAt("1", true);

setDataValidation.docstring:
Set data validation for a range of cells.

@param range - The Excel range to apply validation to (e.g., "A1:B10")
@param validationType - Type of validation (List, WholeNumber, Decimal, Date, Time, TextLength, Custom, FormulaList)
@param operator - Comparison operator (Equal, NotEqual, GreaterThan, etc.)
@param options - Validation configuration options
@param errorStyle - Error display style (Stop, Warning, Information)

@example
// List validation with dropdown
sheet.setDataValidation("B3:B10", DataValidationType.List, DataValidationOperator.Equal, {
  listSource: ["Apple", "Banana", "Orange"],
  inCellDropdown: true
});

freezeFirstColumns.docstring:
Freezes the first columns from the left side of the sheet.
@param count - The number of columns to freeze from the left
@example sheet.freezeFirstColumns(1); // Freeze the first column (column A)

setColumnVisibleAt.docstring:
Set visibility of the column specified by columnLetter.
WARNING: Do NOT hide columns that contain data used by charts unless explicitly requested by the user. Hiding chart source data causes charts to render blank/white.
@example setColumnVisibleAt("A", true);

setRangeFormatting.docstring:
Set the format of a range of cells.
Generally speaking, it's much better to set the format at the same time as the value to prevent forgetting to format later.
However, for bulk formatting jobs, use this function.
@example setRangeFormatting("A1:B10", FormatType.Number);

getPivotTableHandle.docstring:
Get a pivot table handle for modification.
Returns a PivotTableHandle object with methods to query and modify the pivot table.

Use this when you need to:
- Add/remove fields from an existing pivot table
- Change aggregation functions
- Rename value field labels
- Get the current pivot configuration

@param name - The string name of the pivot table (e.g., "SalesPivot")
@returns PivotTableHandle object with methods like addField(), removeField(), getConfig(), etc.
@example
const pt = sheet.getPivotTableHandle('SalesPivot');
pt.addField('Region', 'row');
pt.changeAggregation('Sum of Sales', 'count');

applyConditionalFormatting.docstring:
Apply conditional formatting to a range of cells.

Number format conditions:
- Positive/negative: "[Green]#,##0.00;[Red]-#,##0.00"
- Positive/negative/zero: "[Green]#,##0.00;[Red]-#,##0.00;[Blue]0.00"

Visual conditional formatting: 2-color scale, 3-color scale, Data bar, Icon sets
ONLY USE this function TO APPLY CONDITIONAL FORMATTING. DO NOT use your own logic.

@example sheet.applyConditionalFormatting("B1:B10", "3-color scale", { minColor: "#FF0000", midColor: "#FFFF00", maxColor: "#00FF00" });
@example sheet.applyConditionalFormatting("C1:C10", "Data bar", { barColor: "#638EC6", showBarOnly: false });
@example sheet.applyConditionalFormatting("D1:D10", "Icon sets", { iconSetType: "3TrafficLights" });

applyConditionalFormatting.signature:
applyConditionalFormatting(
    range: string,
    style: ConditionalFormattingStyle,
    options?: ConditionalFormattingOptions
  ): void;

